        <h4>Master’s and undergraduate theses</h4>
        <p>Some Master’s and undergraduate programs offer students an option to deposit their theses or capstone projects in Academic Commons. Consult your program administrator or faculty advisor for specific program policies.</p>

        <h4>Alumni theses</h4>
        <p>Graduates of Columbia University and its affiliates can deposit their dissertation or thesis in Academic Commons with approval from the degree-granting program. Contact the administrator of your degree program to request permission to deposit.</p>

        <h4>Thesis embargoes</h4>
        <p>Degree programs requiring or encouraging students to deposit their thesis in Academic Commons usually offer an embargo option, which allows a student to request a delay to the public release of their thesis for a limited period of time after deposit. During the embargo period, descriptive information about the work is publicly accessible in Academic Commons and the Columbia Libraries catalog, CLIO, but the thesis itself is not available. Embargo options vary by program and students should consult their degree program’s policies.</p>

        <h4>Embargo changes</h4>
        <p>Authors who wish to make changes to the embargo on their thesis in Academic Commons should contact the degree-program administrator with their request. If the request is approved, the program administrator will direct Academic Commons staff to change the embargo.</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Columbia Graduate School of Arts and Sciences (GSAS) authors can contact the Dissertation Office at <a href="mailto:dissertations@columbia.edu">dissertations@columbia.edu</a> to request changes to an embargo.</li>
          <li>Graduates of all other doctoral, Master’s, and undergraduate programs should contact the appropriate degree-program administrator to request changes to an embargo.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Embargo changes in ProQuest</h4>
        <p>Authors who deposited a thesis to ProQuest must also contact ProQuest directly to request changes to the availability of their work in the ProQuest dissertation and thesis database. Contact ProQuest at <a href="mailto:disspub@proquest.com">disspub@proquest.com</a>.</p>

        <h4>Other student works</h4>
        <p>Academic Commons requires departmental approval for deposits of student works that are not covered by a thesis deposit policy.</p>

        <h2 id="terms-of-use">Terms of Use</h2>

